Date: 0/0/1972
Source: From Beads to Banknotes
Author: Hargreaves
Vol / Page: 78
Edition:
Quote: The Southland Treasury had no legal liability for the payment of the notes if issued as they had never been sanctioned by law, and would circulate merely as the personal promissory note of whoever signed them. It is no wonder, then, that the Otago Daily Times called them `Southland Shinplasters'.
